data.title: Webster Youth Leagues
data.text:
Northcoast Travel Basketball League

Northcoast travel basketball is only open to 3rd â€“ 8th grade students who reside within the Webster School District. Travel basketball is a major commitment including two nights of practice per week (dependent on age level), weekend games and tournaments in and out of Monroe County from mid October to early March.

This level of basketball requires prior experience and well developed skills. Tryouts are conducted and evaluated by Northcoast, local high school, and college coaches. The approximate player fee is $250.00 to $350.00. All candidates are notified within two weeks of last tryout. It is mandatory that players attend both tryout dates. Registration for tryouts begin in early August, tryouts will take place in September. To register online click here

Webster Basketball Association League

WBA (Webster Basketball Association) is a Webster instructional house league for boys and girls. The first day will be an evaluation day to test skill levels. Kids will be placed on a team and will work on drills for the first couple weeks. Game play will start in December and players will have 30 minutes of both practice and league play. Players in 1st - 2nd grade will be using lower rims. Please have your child wear their boots and bring sneakers and a water bottle each week. We also ask that your child brings their own basketball due to health and safety concerns. This league can't run without parent volunteers, please email Julie Schillaci at jschillaci@ci.webster.ny.us if you are able to coach this year.

Please email recreation supervisor if you are available and willing to coach. To register online on click here.
